<p>Just mentioning a little m4 script I wrote a little while ago.
ax_check_mysql is used to find a valid MySQL installation, and gives
you the binary, include, and plugin directories.</p>
<p>If you have an autoconf project, and you need MySQL, definitely consider
it!</p>
<p><a class="reference external" href="http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/ax_check_mysql.html#ax_check_mysql">http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf-archive/ax_check_mysql.html#ax_check_mysql</a></p>
